<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-10T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="727" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/105: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stockton</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-10T17:00:00+01:00">April 10, 1931—5
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received April 10—2:10 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>34. Referring to my telegram number 26, April 2, 1 p.m., Foreign Office
                            has formally advised me its readiness to exchange ratifications and has
                            inquired when Legation will be prepared to do so.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockton</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>